PACIFIC
AIRLINES
FLIGHT SCHEDULES
Effective April 26, 1970
HATIOHAL
AIRPORT

Northern California's own
Community Airline
Some 253 Northern California communities, large
and small, are now being served by Golden Pacific
Airlines through sixteen airport cities, from Eureka to
Visalia. (We also fly to Reno, Nevada.)
Our objective, primarily, is to strengthen the
economic and cultural bonds between each of the
253 communities and San Francisco. At the same
time, we also provide regular service between many
of the communities, either direct or via connections
at San Francisco and the other airport cities in
our system.
On Golden Pacific you'll fly the elegant Beech 99
Airliner, the only aircraft designed specifically for
this type of service. It's fast, smooth, and luxurious.
And all operations are geared to full major airline
standards.
If you're going to or from any of the 253 GPA
communities in Northern California, served via the
sixteen GPA airport cities, the only sensible way is
through the air on Golden Pacific.
In our Beech 99s, it's a great new experience.
SAN FRANCISCO
